# weave.word — what a weave IS: the chains a being reads in a moment, folded into its view.
# Axiom: it bottoms out in the host (the reels one fold read, sealed on Act.innerFace.weave). Descends from
# word.word, base.word, chain.word, history.word, fold.word, being.word. Every word grounded (weave,
# fold, chain, history, being). `moment` is a being's fold at the head (now=head), not a tick of the
# clock. The deeper world, the one beings' folds AGREE on, waits for `being`, the perspective that
# makes agreement mean anything.

A fold is the present of one chain. A weave is the chains a being sees in one moment — those it may see, and those where it stands. A moment is the being's present, the one view folded from its weave: each chain's fold, in the place the being stands.
A fold is one chain made present; a weave, the chains seen; a moment, the view folded from them, and kept.
